{title: Morning}
{artist: Jim Ed Brown}
{composer: Written by Willis Graham}

[G]Here in this room this narrow room where life began
When we were [C]young last [G]night
I [D7]feel your back pressed close to me
And [C]hear your steady breathing [D7]as you [G]sleep
Then as the first soft glow of dawn
Moves silver grey like paint [C]along the [G]wall
I [D7]touch your hand and feel your ring
And [C]know this night is [D7]all we'll ever [G]have
Suddenly I look into your [D7]sleepy eyes
You breathe my name and it just seems to [C]dangle [G]there
Then I feel your fingers running [D7]through my mind
Jumbling up my thoughts to leave them [C]tangled [G]there
I know so well that this is all there is
And when we leave this [C]room it's [G]gone
My [D7]mind is clear as we walk down
The [C]crooked little steps to [D7]the front [G]door
A ray of sun that ricochets
From off the rooftop lights our [C]stumbling [G]way
I [D7]touch your hand and feel your ring
And [C]know this night is [D7]all we'll ever [G]have
Repeat #3  x2